This bug actually made the program get stuck in an infinite loop,
causing it to utilize CPU at 100%, for two hours!!!. That was some
dangerous stuff, good thing I wasnt billed by CPU usage. I wonder if
this is a problem with zqlite though, I remember seeing a mutex inside a
loop.

Edit: Actually no, the reason is more stupid. On the deploy
script, I accidentally uncommented a line, so it resulted
as such:

  zig build --release=safe
  zig build

Which means it is essentially building it twice,
but the created binary is a debug build. A debug
build would normally be fine even for a production site,
just slower. But on debug builds, I enabled auto page
reloads, where the server periodically pings the client
with server-sent events. I usually open a bunch
of tabs for thread I wanted to read, so this
created a DOS'ing effect on my own site.

I think that's what happened, at least
based on the nginx logs.
